Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.98,0:00:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.57,0:00:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hurry up,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.78,0:00:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their Duel's gonna start without us!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.24,0:00:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, we're goin' the right way, ain't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.74,0:00:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we just follow the hoof prints, we won't go wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.29,0:00:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I must witness this Duel with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.75,0:00:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.71,0:00:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.01,0:01:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.27,0:01:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.73,0:01:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.74,0:01:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.67,0:01:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.76,0:01:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.46,0:02:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yugi vs Rafael - The Impregnable Guardian Deck"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oi, Otogi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.77,0:02:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Step it up on the accelerator!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.65,0:02:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ain't gonna catch up \Nwith Yugi at this pace!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.49,0:02:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right then! In that case, get ready to fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on tight, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.35,0:02:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otogi! You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't leave us behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.78,0:03:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.24,0:03:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand over Professor Hopkins!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.37,0:03:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have already set the professor free.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He should have already gotten home by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As our death match is about to start, there's no need for an escape route!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.65,0:04:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very honored, Yugi Mutou, to be able to Duel with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.57,0:04:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a True Duelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.87,0:04:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can {\i1}you{\i0} be a True Duelist?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.24,0:04:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were a "True Duelist",
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you wouldn't be using the power of the Duel Monsters for your own evil intentions!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.92,0:04:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we are {\i1}evil{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.96,0:04:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you then, Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your definition of "justice"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.71,0:04:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My definition of justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are both comrades walking on paths we believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In our hearts, we have our own version of "justice."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.22,0:04:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The path that we of Doma are walking towards...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.47,0:04:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it for good or evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that matter, it shall soon be decided by huge historical changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.90,0:04:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Historical changes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.77,0:04:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.86,0:05:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amidst the changes, there is only one thing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.15,0:05:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can only bet on the justice before our eyes and our lives at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.57,0:05:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dueling with full strength... with death in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.01,0:05:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.56,0:05:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Be careful, Other Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.89,0:05:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's not normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it, Partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.57,0:05:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That murderous aura...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.40,0:05:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's like I'm being stalked by a wild beast...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This guy is strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.07,0:05:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall attack first.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.29,0:05:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Continuous Magic, Treasure of Guardian God!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.00,0:06:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By discarding five cards I have on hand, I can draw two cards from my deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In my coming turns, I can draw two cards instead of one!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A card that allows one to draw more cards...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.51,0:06:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even at the expense of discarding five cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is he aiming to get The Barrier of Orichalcos?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon a Defense Position Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.85,0:06:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set another reverse card, and I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.27,0:06:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I have no cards in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.27,0:06:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Yugi, are you relieved now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not have The Barrier of Orichalcos in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His hand is at zero...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once I destroy his face-down Defensive Monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.83,0:06:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}this Duel will be under control!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.08,0:06:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Good...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I polymerize Illusion Beast Gazelle and Berfomet from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Summon Winged Phantom Beast Chimera to the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.39,0:06:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the attacking power Chimera possesses, it can easily destroy any ordinary Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.31,0:07:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Chimera! Attack his Defense Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.15,0:07:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chimera Impact Dash!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.36,0:07:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.41,0:07:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Backup Gardna has a Defense of 2200!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.99,0:07:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Chimera's Attack Points can't touch him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An ordinary attack won't do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.37,0:07:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me your {\i1}strongest{\i0} attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.92,0:07:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That again...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.01,0:07:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Equipment Magic, Gravity Axe!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the special effect of Gravity Axe!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.89,0:07:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.90,0:07:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guardian Grarl is a Monster that can be Summoned when Gravity Axe is on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.11,0:07:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And because of the Effect of Backup Gardna,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.28,0:07:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can attach the Equipment Card, Gravity Axe, to Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.16,0:07:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,3000 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.08,0:08:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Swift Cleave Attack!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.71,0:08:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chimera was beaten this easily...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to Chimera's Effect, I can Summon Berfomet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.01,0:08:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This won't do any damage to my Guardian Deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.39,0:08:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guardian Deck...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, my Monsters will risk their lives to protect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise, I'll protect these Monsters as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.86,0:08:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You say you will protect these Monsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.09,0:08:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The professor is sleeping very soundly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.51,0:08:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't seem to have any injuries, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.42,0:08:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu, take a look at this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I might find some information on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.89,0:08:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After some searching...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.85,0:09:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? There's information about them online?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A news article ten years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the incident that caused a luxury liner to sink?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:11.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was only one survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.32,0:09:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't remember that until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.78,0:09:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I became the U.S. Champion, rumors had it that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first in the U.S. wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.16,0:09:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But someone who used the legendary "Guardian Deck" and who never appeared in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name of that young Guardian Theme user was Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.17,0:09:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, this young boy is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.21,0:09:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.01,0:09:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebecca!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.88,0:09:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me go, Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.51,0:09:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi will surely win.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's believe in him and wait for him to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.72,0:09:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.65,0:09:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you even begin to grasp how strong the bond between myself and these Monsters is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.44,0:09:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't be able to comprehend it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:09:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds so shallow, Rafael.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.61,0:10:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Duelist who believes in his guardian cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.33,0:10:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural for anyone to believe in their own deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.91,0:10:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.42,0:10:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}These cards...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.92,0:10:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They're worn out from overuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.34,0:10:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, to ensure I can't differentiate them from my other cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.05,0:10:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've pasted new covers on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.01,0:10:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this does not change the fact that they have supported me for a very long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These cards hold a true power - They rescued me from the abyss I was in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.57,0:10:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi... No, Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.41,0:10:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I knew of your existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.74,0:10:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have held some strange feelings towards you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.21,0:10:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are both people being manipulated by fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People manipulated by fate...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.71,0:10:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place greatly resembles the place where I lived with my Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.55,0:11:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a no-man island floating on land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.99,0:11:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here, Big Brod'er!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.45,0:11:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What have we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.70,0:11:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hurry up an' open it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.04,0:11:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Isn't this Guardian Eatos?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've wanted this card so badly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Julien and me worked really hard to find this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sonia!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.59,0:11:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big Brother, happy birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.13,0:11:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happy birf'day!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.09,0:11:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sonia, Julien, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.52,0:11:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wh-What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.81,0:11:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.60,0:11:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:11:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's up with the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've caught you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.15,0:12:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I caught ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.45,0:12:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.95,0:12:06.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big Brod'er?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.34,0:12:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big Brod'er!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.30,0:12:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sonia!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.51,0:12:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Julien!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.64,0:12:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Big Brod'er!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.52,0:12:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sonia!! Julien!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Papa! Mama!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.81,0:13:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sonia! Julien!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.74,0:13:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That accident happened too suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.53,0:13:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fate took away all that I had in a single moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Eatos... Was it you who protected me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.19,0:14:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I'm alive, maybe my family is alive somewhere too."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that in mind, I strove to stay alive on that no-man island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.12,0:14:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever been unable to speak to anyone for three whole years?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever endured the loneliness of being unable to touch anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.36,0:14:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kept me going and prevented me from going crazy from all the loneliness...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.12,0:14:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...were these cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were my friends and family at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That murderous aura surrounding him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can that be coming from the Monsters that want to protect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.48,0:15:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.44,0:15:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you love your cards so dearly,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why are you helping Doma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nameless Pharaoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.36,0:15:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.61,0:15:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humans can't fight against the "fate" that exists in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've experienced that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.42,0:16:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that there are ignorant people in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.13,0:16:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who do not\N know the existence of "fate."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.39,0:16:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Young lad, he who leads the Duel Monsters into battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.73,0:16:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once thy seeith clearly, thou shalt return to my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I returned back to this world miraculously.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.16,0:17:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what was waiting for me in my former world...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.04,0:17:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was endless despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whereabouts of my family remains unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.84,0:17:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that was left were my relatives, who took my Dad's inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.80,0:17:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And those who wanted to share in my fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that I had stayed alive to return to such a place...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.11,0:17:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nameless Pharaoh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.77,0:17:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did your soul revive after thousands of years?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was my whole family wiped out in seconds...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...leaving me alone to live in this malicious world?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.12,0:17:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't answer my questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is but one way to answer to "fate."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.48,0:18:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rafael...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why were you the only one to survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.86,0:18:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do you want to know the answer to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I shall guide you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.20,0:18:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to "fate..."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.66,0:18:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to know the answer, you'll have to accept your own destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.58,0:18:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can only watch carefully to see where your fate will bring you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.33,0:18:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean that you're also fighting your own fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.88,0:18:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But fate will only allow\N one of us to stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.84,0:18:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have no wish to disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.09,0:18:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.73,0:18:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That hurts~!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.60,0:18:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd die~!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.31,0:18:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has the Duel started?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.44,0:18:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.44,0:18:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card, Twinkle Five-Star!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.45,0:19:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Twinkle Five-Star card can only be used when there is a Five-Star Monster on your side of the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Five Stars will Summon the Kuriboh Brothers to the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the Kuriboh Siblings!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.51,0:19:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are these the Monsters that protect you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.97,0:19:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be careless, Rafael.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Special Effect of Kuriba!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.60,0:19:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kuriboh Siblings will combine to form a Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.60,0:19:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuribabylon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.61,0:19:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I activate Pump Up from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.53,0:19:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card can double the Attack Power of a Monster for a full turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuribabylon, attack Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.12,0:19:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card I placed in the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.83,0:19:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rescuer from the Grave!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.63,0:19:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Magic Card that can be activated even when it's in the Graveyard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.13,0:20:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rescuer from the Grave...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.14,0:20:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By removing five cards in the Graveyard out of the game, the battle with your opponent is invalid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.06,0:20:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've said this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.02,0:20:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That I'll protect these Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.73,0:20:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order to have this defense...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.52,0:20:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was why he discarded his hand in the start...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's truly strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.86,0:20:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I'm quite disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.49,0:20:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that turn earlier, both our Monsters had the same Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.41,0:20:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Given that situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.53,0:20:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your precious Monsters would have gone into the Grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.62,0:20:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forgive anyone who belittles his Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set two cards face-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.88,0:20:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate a Continuous Magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.88,0:20:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purity of the Cemetery!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.39,0:20:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The effect of Purity of the Cemetery is that, for every Monster sleeping in your Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.56,0:20:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will be dealt 100 points in damage every turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This effect is destroyed once there is a Monster in my Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this guy really intending not to get any of his Monsters sent into the Graveyard?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.41,0:21:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And let me tell you one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.37,0:21:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never use The Barrier of Orichalcos in this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I don't use that card,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.54,0:21:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll still be able to defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.75,0:21:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your little servants are now in Attack Position after the attack was nullified earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.47,0:21:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guardian Grarl has an Attack of 3000 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.02,0:21:33.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a difference of 2700 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.68,0:21:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this attack hits, it will be vital damage to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.23,0:21:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead, Guardian Grarl!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Swift Cleave Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.64,0:22:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.00,0:22:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.61,0:22:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.68,0:22:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.16,0:22:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.34,0:22:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.49,0:23:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.01,0:23:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.58,0:23:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each betting on the 'justice' that they believe in,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.71,0:23:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The violent battle between Yugi and Rafael continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.30,0:23:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rafael, who has a strong bond with his Monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.67,0:23:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Risks his Life Points in order to save them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.51,0:23:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But is he really intending not to use The Barrier of Orichalcos at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.31,0:23:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the truth about Doma and their aim is revealed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, "The Truth about Doma"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.44,0:23:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
